[goal]
Turn raw founder notes about CRUMB into a sharp X thread and a short landing-page value proposition.

[context]
- Raw notes are repetitive and mix product vision with implementation details.
- The core message is: CRUMB is the copy-paste AI handoff format.
- Audience is technical founders, builders, and agent-heavy users.
- Strongest pain point is losing context when switching AI tools.
- Strongest proof is a before/after cross-tool handoff demo.

[constraints]
- Lead with the pain, not the spec.
- Avoid academic wording like "semantic context container".
- Keep the thread punchy and screenshot-friendly.
- Keep landing copy direct and simple.

[notes]
